WEBVTT

00:02.235 --> 00:04.003
So, this morning,
I looked in the mirror
and I realized

00:04.005 --> 00:06.505
I don't have a job,

00:06.507 --> 00:09.341
A girlfriend,
or any money
in the bank.

00:09.343 --> 00:11.377
And if
I'm not careful,

00:11.379 --> 00:13.012
I could become
a failure.

00:14.514 --> 00:16.615
Uh, "become"?

00:16.617 --> 00:19.218
Lacey, nolan's
being vulnerable.

00:19.220 --> 00:21.420
The least you
could do is stop texting
while you insult him.

00:21.422 --> 00:22.721
I'm sorry.

00:22.723 --> 00:25.057
Uh, "become"?

00:25.059 --> 00:27.793
Come on, guys.
This is a support group.

00:27.795 --> 00:29.795
Would anyone care
to support nolan?

00:29.797 --> 00:31.497
I'll jump in there.

00:31.499 --> 00:35.768
Nolan,
I support you 110%.

00:35.770 --> 00:38.203
If you believe you can be
a complete failure,

00:38.205 --> 00:40.472
I say go for it.

00:40.474 --> 00:42.775
Thank you, ed.

00:42.777 --> 00:45.377
All right, all right,
enough with this dog pile
of support.

00:45.379 --> 00:47.146
Just because you don't
have everything you want

00:47.148 --> 00:48.580
Doesn't mean
you're a failure.

00:48.582 --> 00:50.783
Oh, my god.
It so does.

00:50.785 --> 00:53.485
No, no. It just means
you have to try harder.

00:53.487 --> 00:55.087
Look at me.

00:55.089 --> 00:57.089
I have submitted
half a dozen research papers,

00:57.091 --> 00:59.358
Hoping to get
a government grant,
and so far, nothing.

00:59.360 --> 01:01.060
Do I dwell on it?

01:01.062 --> 01:03.529
Do I wish bad things
on the winners?

01:03.531 --> 01:05.531
Sometimes.

01:05.533 --> 01:07.399
But I don't consider
myself a failure.

01:07.401 --> 01:08.667
Really?

01:08.669 --> 01:11.637
What are you
waiting for?

01:11.639 --> 01:13.439
You people
have lost perspective.

01:13.441 --> 01:16.175
You may not have
what you want, but you
have what you need.

01:16.177 --> 01:17.342
Oh, yeah.
Easy for you to say.

01:17.344 --> 01:18.844
I'm a man
in my late 20s

01:18.846 --> 01:22.114
And I have yet to summer
on martha's vineyard.

01:22.116 --> 01:25.551
And yet you hide your pain
for minutes at a time.

01:25.553 --> 01:28.220
Lacey, you still
on community service
for your probation?

01:28.222 --> 01:29.621
I have, like,
300 hours left,

01:29.623 --> 01:32.391
But I figure I can
knock it out in a weekend.

01:32.393 --> 01:34.760
There's a soup kitchen
that sam and I help out
on the holidays.

01:34.762 --> 01:37.329
I want you all to spend
a couple days there before
our next session.

01:37.331 --> 01:39.565
- Oh, man.
- I can't, I'm busy
this weekend.

01:39.567 --> 01:42.334
I have a class in...

01:42.336 --> 01:46.171
Making up better excuses
on the fly.

01:46.173 --> 01:48.440
I'll count it as a full
session on your records.

01:48.442 --> 01:50.742
<i>Trust me, it'll be</i>
<i>very fulfilling.</i>

01:50.744 --> 01:52.444
See you all
next Tuesday.

01:55.116 --> 01:57.850
Nah, I got to go back
through those research grants

01:57.852 --> 01:59.485
And figure out what
the hell I'm doing wrong.

01:59.487 --> 02:01.286
- I feel like such a...
- Failure?

02:01.288 --> 02:03.255
- No.
- Person of little success?

02:03.257 --> 02:04.890
Closer.

02:05.892 --> 02:07.726
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

02:09.896 --> 02:12.664
