tell you that?

12:23.810 --> 12:25.844
Why, no, she did not
tell me that.

12:27.813 --> 12:29.080
I mean, you're cool
with it, right?

12:29.082 --> 12:32.217
Am I cool with it?
Let's see.

12:32.219 --> 12:35.186
- Let me run down
the cool checklist.
- All right.

12:35.188 --> 12:37.489
You got no money,
no job,

12:37.491 --> 12:39.858
- And you're living in
the house that I pay for.
- Ahem.

12:39.860 --> 12:41.993
On the other hand,
you are super arrogant.

12:41.995 --> 12:43.828
So, no, dude,
I am not cool with it.

12:43.830 --> 12:47.031
- Check, please.
- Okay.

12:47.033 --> 12:49.234
Well, this
is super awkward.

12:49.236 --> 12:52.270
Um, listen, jen
gave you enough cash

12:52.272 --> 12:54.839
To cover my portion
of the tab, right?

12:54.841 --> 12:56.007
Yeah.

12:56.009 --> 12:57.942
Did she give you
a little extra

12:57.944 --> 12:59.878
So I could, like,
grab a sandwich
or something?

12:59.880 --> 13:01.246
I didn't eat
anything.

13:01.248 --> 13:04.849
It's not jen's money.
It's my money.

13:04.851 --> 13:07.786
And I am this close
to taking off my
store-bought belt.

13:15.161 --> 13:17.796
Aren't you
a little overdressed
for a soup kitchen?

13:17.798 --> 13:20.498
Are you kidding me?
I'm so boosting morale
around here.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.801
Everyone's, like,
"this place isn't so bad.

13:22.803 --> 13:25.103
Check out that
hot piece of ass
ladling soup."

13:27.273 --> 13:31.342
The ironic thing was
I felt I was better
than everybody else.

13:31.344 --> 13:33.978
Oh, my god.
I felt the same way.

13:33.980 --> 13:36.014
I didn't realize
that we're all

13:36.016 --> 13:39.250
Just a couple of
bad breaks away from
sleeping on the street.

13:39.252 --> 13:41.252
Oh, I don't sleep
on the street.

13:41.254 --> 13:44.155
No, I sleep in an old pipe
on a construction site.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.859
But this year
I hope to summer

13:47.861 --> 13:49.961
At a mcdonald's playland
near the beach.

13:52.398 --> 13:54.499
That's your
martha's vineyard.

13:54.501 --> 13:57.135
Here, please, I have
to give you some more money.

13:57.137 --> 13:59.904
No, no, please.
You've done too
much already.

13:59.906 --> 14:01.840
I feel guilty
that I have so much.

14:01.842 --> 14:03.541
Here's another 20.

14:03.543 --> 14:05.476
It's all I have left.

14:07.313 --> 14:08.947
I got to get back
to the line.

14:08.949 --> 14:11.883
You know, I envy you,
patrick.

14:11.885 --> 14:13.084
I wish someone
had told me

14:13.086 --> 14:14.619
That pride comes
before a fall.

14:14.621 --> 14:18.256
Or, in our case, before
the fall collection.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.459
Auf wiedersehen.

14:26.298 --> 14:29.400
Ed, come on.
You're supposed
to be working here.

14:29.402 --> 14:31.936
Who died and put
you in charge?

14:33.038 --> 14:35.206
I don't have
to serve here.

14:35.208 --> 14:38.910
I served in a little
soup kitchen called vietnam.

14:38.912 --> 14:43.181
The only difference was,
in 'nam, pajamas were free.

14:43.183 --> 14:45.617
But you had to kill
the people in 'em.

14:58.264 --> 15:00.098
Hey.

15:01.300 --> 15:02.901
What do you want?

15:02.903 --> 15:05.169
Did I hear you say
you served in 'nam?

15:07.306 --> 15:08.907
Which branch?

15:08.909 --> 15:11.242
Army.

15:11.244 --> 15:12.577
Me, too.

15:12.579 --> 15:14.345
Desert storm.

15:14.347 --> 15:17.015
Loved to serve, but...

15:17.017 --> 15:19.584
Sure was a long way
from texas.

15:19.586 --> 15:22.921
Texas is your home, too?

15:22.923 --> 15:26.124
When I had a home.

15:26.126 --> 15:28.159
Oh, gee, I'm sorry.

15:32.331 --> 15:34.599
Thanks for coming,
but please tell caroline

15:34.601 --> 15:36.401
That I can't help her
with her fear

15:36.403 --> 15:39.237
Of leaving her house
if she keeps sending
her assistant in

15:39.239 --> 15:40.972
To do her therapy
sessions for her.

15:44.343 --> 15:46.277
- Hey, charlie.
- Hey.

15:46.279 --> 15:48.646
Listen, I'm really sorry
about the other night.

15:48.648 --> 15:51.516
And I get it.
Sex is off the table...

15:51.518 --> 15:53.117
And the floor and the roof
of your building.

15:53.119 --> 15:55.019
All the usual places.

15:55.021 --> 15:57.155
Thanks and I get it.

15:57.157 --> 15:58.589
I mean, this new dynamic
in our friendship

15:58.591 --> 16:00.091
Is making things
a little confusing,

16:00.093 --> 16:01.559
So why don't we just go in

16:01.561 --> 16:04.095
And deal with the other issues
in your life, not you and me.

16:04.097 --> 16:06.464
No problem.
Believe me, I got
plenty to talk about.

16:07.700 --> 16:10.335
So, tell me
what's going on.

16:10.337 --> 16:13.671
- You're ruining my life.
- Okay, didn't I just...

16:13.673 --> 16:15.573
I'm kidding.
It was a joke.

16:16.642 --> 16:18.142
Here's the big headline.

16:18.144 --> 16:21.679
Unemployed sean
is moving in with
alimony jen.

16:21.681 --> 16:24.582
Oh, wow.
Well, you must really
resent that.

16:24.584 --> 16:26.684
But it's her life
and her choices

16:26.686 --> 16:28.720
And you have
to accept that.

16:28.722 --> 16:30.688
I know I should,
but I can't.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.590
Why am I always
attracted to women

16:32.592 --> 16:35.426
Who don't have the sense
to know who they should
or shouldn't be with?

16:35.428 --> 16:37.595
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
- What?

16:37.597 --> 16:40.398
That wasn't just about jen.
That was about you and me.

16:40.400 --> 16:42.700
Oh, right, I'm sorry.
I didn't realize
I was doing that.

16:42.702 --> 16:44.769
I will keep
them separate.

16:44.771 --> 16:46.637
Here we go.
( sighs )

16:46.639 --> 16:48.573
Jen made a decision
that I don't agree
with at all,

16:48.575 --> 16:52.176
But it affects me and I have
no say in the matter.

16:52.178 --> 16:53.611
How come you women
don't give a crap

16:53.613 --> 16:55.513
About anyone's feelings
but your own?

16:56.782 --> 16:58.583
Hold it, hold it,
hold it.

16:58.585 --> 17:00.051
What?

17:00.053 --> 17:01.619
You're including me again.

17:01.621 --> 17:04.188
Oh, my god.
I'm so sorry.

17:04.190 --> 17:07.225
Obviously, our relationship
or lack of one

17:07.227 --> 17:09.727
Is weighing heavily on me
and it's bleeding through.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.096
But I'm aware of it now
and I've got a handle on it,

17:12.098 --> 17:13.765
So I think
we can continue.

17:13.767 --> 17:15.666
Well said.
Thank you.

17:15.668 --> 17:18.636
Now, what is
your issue with jen?

17:18.638 --> 17:20.605
Well, it's very simple.

17:20.607 --> 17:22.707
What the hell
is your problem, lady?

17:22.709 --> 17:24.342
We should have sex
and be together!

17:27.212 --> 17:28.813
That time I knew
what I was doing.

17:34.586 --> 17:36.454
Hey, guys.

17:36.456 --> 17:40.224
And hopefully that will help
us explore some core issues.

17:40.226 --> 17:42.493
Charlie:
<i>Ernesto, you said...</i>

17:42.495 --> 17:46.597
Your dad's "playboys"
from the 1980s.

17:46.599 --> 17:49.634
The women were
mesmerizing.

17:49.636 --> 17:51.369
And I also learned
a lot about

17:51.371 --> 17:53.671
Where to place
my living room speakers.

17:55.674 --> 17:59.544
Donovan, you said,
"oh, the places you'll go!"

17:59.546 --> 18:01.779
I sure wish dr. Seuss
woulda written a book

18:01.781 --> 18:03.714
About the places
I shouldn't have gone.

18:04.817 --> 18:07.752
Like a gas station
with a gun in my hand.

18:09.354 --> 18:10.755
Or disneyland.

18:10.757 --> 18:14.525
$10 for a piece of pizza
and    <i>i</i>in jail.

18:14.527 --> 18:16.160
You carjacked a bus.

18:16.162 --> 18:17.762
They overcharge
for pepperoni.

18:17.764 --> 18:19.730
I still agree with you.

18:20.699 --> 18:24.635
Wayne, you said
"alice in wonderland."

18:24.637 --> 18:26.471
I've always
loved that book.

18:26.473 --> 18:28.473
There's just something special
about a little girl

18:28.475 --> 18:30.842
Who falls down a hole
and can't get out.

18:33.679 --> 18:35.246
Congratulations, wayne.

18:35.248 --> 18:37.381
You just made a creepy book
a whole lot creepier.

18:38.517 --> 18:40.685
What books did you read
as a kid, charlie?

18:40.687 --> 18:43.754
Comic books.
Mostly "batman."

18:43.756 --> 18:47.358
If batman catches
the joker every time,

18:47.360 --> 18:49.660
Why doesn't the joker
move to a different city?

18:49.662 --> 18:52.563
- Because
the joker's insane.
- Mm.

18:52.565 --> 18:54.265
And the definition of insanity
is doing the same thing

18:54.267 --> 18:56.634
Over and over, expecting
a different result.

18:56.636 --> 18:59.904
I kept killing people,
hoping the voices would stop.

18:59.906 --> 19:02.740
Never worked.

19:02.742 --> 19:04.742
That is a perfect
example, wayne.

19:04.744 --> 19:06.544
And I know you don't
hear the voices anymore,

19:06.546 --> 19:09.480
Considering you're on
enough thorazine to kill
a baby elephant.

19:09.482 --> 19:10.848
I am?

19:12.651 --> 19:14.552
And that kind of
destructive behavior

19:14.554 --> 19:16.487
Is not just limited
to killing sprees.

19:16.489 --> 19:18.523
Oh, guilty as charged.

19:18.525 --> 19:20.691
When I first got locked up,
I had a crush on a young man.

19:20.693 --> 19:22.860
He had problems.
But no matter what I did,

19:22.862 --> 19:25.630
He would not change,
so I had to just walk away.

19:25.632 --> 19:28.533
Granted, he was in
the same cell, so it was
only, like, four feet.

19:28.535 --> 19:31.602
But you get
what I'm saying.

19:31.604 --> 19:33.738
Who is it?
I'll kill him.

19:33.740 --> 19:35.640
Oh, donovan.

19:35.642 --> 19:37.642
You already did.

19:41.713 --> 19:44.782
Well, not everybody's
as healthy as you, cleo.

19:45.751 --> 19:47.618
Some people
never walk away.

19:47.620 --> 19:49.687
Some people just keep
banging their head
against the wall

19:49.689 --> 19:53.891
Over and over
until they finally
realize that...

19:53.893 --> 19:56.761
She's never
gonna change.

19:56.763 --> 19:59.664
When did they
give it to me?

19:59.666 --> 20:01.699
Is it in the waffles?

20:03.335 --> 20:06.504
You're the only one
that gets waffles, wayne.

20:07.739 --> 20:09.540
Then, probably.

20:13.479 --> 20:17.715
Oh, charlie, hey.
I was just gonna
give you a call.

20:17.717 --> 20:20.284
You got to read this.

20:20.286 --> 20:23.454
I will read this
when I wanna read this.

20:23.456 --> 20:26.691
And I will talk
when I wanna talk
and I wanna talk now.

20:26.693 --> 20:28.826
You shut down
our relationship.

20:28.828 --> 20:30.795
I feel hurt
and rejected

20:30.797 --> 20:32.863
And I cannot stand here
and pretend like anything
we do here

20:32.865 --> 20:35.233
Is gonna make me feel better
when just looking at you

20:35.235 --> 20:41.272
<i>I realize that</i>
<i>the healthy thing</i>
<i>is for me to move on.</i>

20:41.274 --> 20:43.641
I don't want
to see you.

20:43.643 --> 20:45.576
I don't want
to talk to you.

20:45.578 --> 20:48.879
- We're done.
- Okay.

20:48.881 --> 20:51.983
- Are you finished?
- Yes.

20:51.985 --> 20:55.286
Now read the paper.

20:55.288 --> 20:56.754
Damn it.

20:56.756 --> 20:57.955
It's all about you,
isn't it?

20:57.957 --> 21:00.658
It's all about
what you want...

21:00.660 --> 21:01.826
And the fact that we got

21:01.828 --> 21:03.928
The big research grant
we applied for

21:03.930 --> 21:05.763
And we're gonna
be working together

21:05.765 --> 21:07.565
For the next
six months.

21:09.801 --> 21:11.936
Aren't you excited?
